</p><p id="Par10">The Hilbert space of these 3 spins is decomposed to two subspaces, <inline-formula id="IEq41"><alternatives><tex-math id="M85">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\mathscr {H}}= \bigoplus \nolimits _{j} {\mathscr {H}}_{j} = {\mathscr {H}}_{3/2} \oplus {\mathscr {H}}_{1/2}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M86"><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="script">H</mml:mi><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mo>&#x02a01;</mml:mo><mml:mi>j</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="script">H</mml:mi><mml:mi>j</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="script">H</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mn>3</mml:mn><mml:mo stretchy="false">/</mml:mo><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:mrow></mml:msub><mml:mo>&#x02295;</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="script">H</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mn>1</mml:mn><mml:mo stretchy="false">/</mml:mo><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:mrow></mml:msub></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="11128_2017_1792_Article_IEq41.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>, where <inline-formula id="IEq42"><alternatives><tex-math id="M87">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\text {dim}({\mathscr {H}}_{3/2})=4$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M88"><mml:mrow><mml:mtext>dim</mml:mtext><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="script">H</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mn>3</mml:mn><mml:mo stretchy="false">/</mml:mo><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:mrow></mml:msub><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mn>4</mml:mn></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="11128_2017_1792_Article_IEq42.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> and <inline-formula id="IEq43"><alternatives><tex-math id="M89">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
