				\begin{document}$$\text {dim}({\mathscr {H}}_{1/2})=4$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M90"><mml:mrow><mml:mtext>dim</mml:mtext><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="script">H</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mn>1</mml:mn><mml:mo stretchy="false">/</mml:mo><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:mrow></mml:msub><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mn>4</mml:mn></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="11128_2017_1792_Article_IEq43.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>. Each subspace <inline-formula id="IEq44"><alternatives><tex-math id="M91">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\mathscr {H}}_{j}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M92"><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="script">H</mml:mi><mml:mi>j</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="11128_2017_1792_Article_IEq44.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> is further decomposed into a product of two <italic>subsystems</italic>, where the first component refers to the <italic>s</italic> label and the second component refers to the <italic>m</italic> label,<disp-formula id="Equ3"><label>3</label><alternatives><tex-math id="M93">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\begin{aligned} {\mathscr {H}}= \bigoplus \limits _{j} {\mathbb {C}}_{\mathbf {s}_{j}} \otimes {\mathbb {C}}_\mathbf{m _{j}}= {\mathbb {C}}_{1} \otimes {\mathbb {C}}_{4} \oplus {\mathbb {C}}_{2} \otimes {\mathbb {C}}_{2}. \end{aligned}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M94" display="block"><mml:mrow><mml:mtable><mml:mtr><mml:mtd columnalign="right"><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="script">H</mml:mi><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:munder><mml:mo>&#x02a01;</mml:mo><mml:mi>j</mml:mi></mml:munder><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="double-struck">C</mml:mi><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="bold">s</mml:mi><mml:mi>j</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:msub><mml:mo>&#x02297;</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="double-struck">C</mml:mi><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="bold">m</mml:mi><mml:mi mathvariant="bold">j</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:msub><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="double-struck">C</mml:mi><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:msub><mml:mo>&#x02297;</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="double-struck">C</mml:mi><mml:mn>4</mml:mn></mml:msub><mml:mo>&#x02295;</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="double-struck">C</mml:mi><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:msub><mml:mo>&#x02297;</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="double-struck">C</mml:mi><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:msub><mml:mo>.</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:mtd></mml:mtr></mml:mtable></mml:mrow></mml:math><graphic xlink:href="11128_2017_1792_Article_Equ3.gif" position="anchor"/></alternatives></disp-formula>We used the bold notation to distinguish the dimension of the space of a label from its value, i.e., <inline-formula id="IEq45"><alternatives><tex-math id="M95">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\mathbf s _{j} = \text {dim}(\{s_{j}\})$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M96"><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="bold">s</mml:mi><mml:mi>j</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mtext>dim</mml:mtext><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">{</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>s</mml:mi><mml:mi>j</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo stretchy="false">}</mml:mo></mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="11128_2017_1792_Article_IEq45.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> and <inline-formula id="IEq46"><alternatives><tex-math id="M97">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
