				\begin{document}$$ j=1/2$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M106"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>j</mml:mi><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn><mml:mo stretchy="false">/</mml:mo><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="11128_2017_1792_Article_IEq49.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>) of 3 identical physical qubits to encode one logical qubit because it is <italic>protected</italic> against collective noise. Explicitly, the logical basis is defined by<disp-formula id="Equ5"><label>5</label><alternatives><tex-math id="M107">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
