				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$U_{\pm }$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M708"><mml:msub><mml:mi>U</mml:mi><mml:mo>&#x000b1;</mml:mo></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="11128_2017_1792_Article_IEq322.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> is an arbitrary rotation from the ground state to the first excited state, where both the torsional and the spin degrees of freedom are considered. Given <inline-formula id="IEq323"><alternatives><tex-math id="M709">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
